true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1224%2C815 3x\" type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=408%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=816%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1224%2C815 3x\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=408%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=816%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1224%2C815 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=408%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=816%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1224%2C815 3x\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1112%2C740 2x\" type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1112%2C740 2x\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1112%2C740 2x\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=556%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1112%2C740 2x\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"New Strava beta\" title=\"New Strava beta\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\"></picture></div><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/03/New-Strava-beta-0eb1e03.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=768%2C574\"><meta itemprop=\"width\" content=\"768\"><meta itemprop=\"height\" content=\"574\"></div><div><p>Published: <time datetime=\"2021-03-24T18:00:59+00:00\">March 24, 2021 at 6:00 pm</time></p><meta itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2021-03-24T18:00:59+00:00\"><meta itemprop=\"dateModified\" content=\"2021-03-24T18:00:11+00:00\"><p></p></div></div><section itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p><span>Strava is planning major changes to the functionality and layout of its app. As part of this, it has just released a beta version of the new layout to a sub-group of its paying subscribers and free users.</span></p><p><span>The updated design applies to both Android and iOS devices, and <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/brand/strava/\">Strava</a> says it should make it easier for users to navigate to the features they’re looking for and will form the basis for the rollout of future additional features.</span></p><p>This comes as part of a series of new functions Strava has already rolled out this year, including a <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/strava-monthly-activity-stats-animation/\">monthly activity stats</a> animation and refinements to <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/strava-personal-heatmap/\">personal heatmaps</a>.</p><p><span>A key update is to the ‘You’ tab which now puts all your activities and stats in one place. Via the You tab, you can track your training, search your workouts and view your profile.</span></p><p><span>The Progress feature under the You tab gives details of recent activities, while the Activities function provides full details for every activity you’ve ever uploaded and lets you zero in or sort activities by sport, distance, time, elevation, date range, and exercise type, such as a race or <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/how-to-ride-100-miles/\">long ride</a>.</span></p><p><span>From the Home screen you can still see the activities of followed users, give kudos and comment.</span></p><p><span>The new Maps tab lets you find popular segments or plot new routes, while a Saved tab lets you see achievements, favourite routes and segments, and Local Legend crowns.</span></p><p><span>A Groups tab gives you the option to join groups and interact with the rest of the Strava community, join challenges and find athletes and brands via clubs.</span></p><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/09/Strava-record-screen-with-sensor-pairing-65d472e.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=249%2C199, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/09/Strava-record-screen-with-sensor-pairing-65d472e.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=499%2C399 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/09/Strava-reco